WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:03.003
Previously on
"Time After Time"...

00:03.046 --> 00:05.918
Tell Wells that if he wants
to see Vanessa alive again,

00:05.962 --> 00:08.051
that I'll need the time machine
and the both of you.

00:08.095 --> 00:10.749
Is this everything
on Project Utopia?

00:10.793 --> 00:12.403
That's what you asked for,
isn't it?

00:12.447 --> 00:14.405
We saw your father
kill Robert Holland.

00:17.060 --> 00:18.583
I found a nurse,
Phyllis Johnson,

00:18.627 --> 00:20.063
who worked on
the project.

00:20.107 --> 00:23.675
I would collect
all the samples for Dr. Monroe.

00:23.719 --> 00:25.112
Don't move the time machine.

00:25.155 --> 00:26.765
Brooke has figured out
a way to hijack it.

00:26.809 --> 00:28.767
What have you done?

00:28.811 --> 00:30.769
Taken the time machine,
just like I said I would.

00:30.813 --> 00:32.945
You have to go back.
Exactly like it's written.

00:32.989 --> 00:35.513
I know what happens.

00:35.557 --> 00:36.949
And now
I'm going to change it.

00:36.993 --> 00:40.257
No, Jane's not
supposed to be with him.

00:40.301 --> 00:42.259
She could ruin everything!

00:45.001 --> 00:48.048
♪♪

00:50.659 --> 00:52.617
Jane!

00:54.141 --> 00:59.059
Jane!

01:00.843 --> 01:04.803
♪♪

01:47.716 --> 01:49.326
Hey!

01:49.370 --> 01:50.936
Over here!

01:55.724 --> 01:57.595
Hey, I see one!

01:59.641 --> 02:01.512
Don't let him
get away!

02:03.949 --> 02:05.908
Stop! Don't run!

02:05.951 --> 02:08.040
♪♪

02:08.084 --> 02:09.955
Stop right there!

02:09.999 --> 02:12.044
Ya, ya!

02:12.088 --> 02:13.916
Ya!

02:21.184 --> 02:24.796
♪♪

02:27.234 --> 02:28.757
No, wait, please.

02:28.800 --> 02:30.541
Please, you don't understand --
this is a mistake.

02:44.947 --> 02:47.906
♪♪

02:50.692 --> 02:54.304
H.G.!

02:54.348 --> 02:57.829
H.G.!

02:59.222 --> 03:03.835
♪♪

03:07.491 --> 03:09.885
H.G.!

03:09.928 --> 03:12.714
Please, I don't have time
for this.

03:12.757 --> 03:14.542
I have done
nothing wrong.

03:14.585 --> 03:15.891
You have no right
to keep me here.

03:15.934 --> 03:18.415
Sure, I do.
You're trespassing.

03:18.459 --> 03:21.026
Trespa-- I have no idea
where I am.

03:21.070 --> 03:22.985
What were you doing
at the radar tower?

03:23.028 --> 03:25.248
At the tower?
I was looking for help.

03:25.292 --> 03:27.555
Look, this is all just
a big misunderstanding.

03:27.598 --> 03:29.774
Now, you must let me go.
I have to...

03:29.818 --> 03:32.081
You have to what?

03:32.124 --> 03:36.346
Am I keeping you
from something?

03:36.390 --> 03:38.653
You really need
to start talking.

03:38.696 --> 03:41.264
Why are you here?

03:41.308 --> 03:42.961
I washed ashore.

03:43.005 --> 03:44.615
Alone?

03:44.659 --> 03:49.316
♪♪

03:50.839 --> 03:53.276
Who else is with you?

03:53.320 --> 03:54.625
No one.

03:54.669 --> 03:56.453
Mm-hmm.

03:56.497 --> 03:58.803
♪♪

04:00.109 --> 04:01.371
What is that?

04:01.415 --> 04:03.547
Something to jog your memory.
Who sent you?

04:03.591 --> 04:04.983
Was it the D.O.D.?

04:05.027 --> 04:06.463
Anders Enterprises?

04:06.507 --> 04:07.986
Anders?

04:08.030 --> 04:09.684
Oh, is that it?

04:09.727 --> 04:14.558
Did Anders send you here
to, uh...

04:14.602 --> 04:16.125
spy on us?

04:16.168 --> 04:17.082
I washed ashore.
No, I'm telling you the truth.

04:17.126 --> 04:18.388
I --

04:18.432 --> 04:19.650
Montgomery, stop it!

04:19.694 --> 04:21.826
Is this any way
to treat a guest?

04:21.870 --> 04:23.306
♪♪

04:23.350 --> 04:25.003
No, sir.

04:25.047 --> 04:27.702
♪♪

04:27.745 --> 04:29.007
You look thirsty.

04:30.879 --> 04:32.097
♪♪

04:32.141 --> 04:33.708
Want something to drink?

04:33.751 --> 04:36.928
♪♪

04:38.626 --> 04:40.062
I'm sorry.

04:40.105 --> 04:41.237
It's not water --
I should've mentioned that.

04:41.281 --> 04:43.674
I'm sorry.
Uh, manners?

04:43.718 --> 04:47.069
I'm Edward --
Dr. Edward Monroe.

04:47.112 --> 04:48.810
And you are?

04:48.853 --> 04:50.028
George.

04:50.072 --> 04:51.334
Wells-ley.

04:51.378 --> 04:52.640
Oh.

04:52.683 --> 04:54.511
That's quite an accent
you have there.

04:54.555 --> 04:57.035
You a long way from home,
aren't you, George?

04:57.079 --> 04:59.560
You could say that.

04:59.603 --> 05:02.127
What brings you
to our little island?

05:02.171 --> 05:06.871
As I've stated, my boat capsized
and I washed ashore -- alone.

05:06.915 --> 05:08.264
♪♪

05:08.308 --> 05:11.049
Now, I must insist
that you let me go.

05:11.093 --> 05:13.617
Where were you headed?

05:13.661 --> 05:14.836
I'm an oceanographer,

05:14.879 --> 05:16.707
and -- and my vessel
turned over.

05:16.751 --> 05:20.145
W-Why were you
off the coast of Maine?

05:21.625 --> 05:24.236
I was, uh,
gathering data

05:24.280 --> 05:28.850
about coastal erosion
and hypothermal circulation.

05:28.893 --> 05:30.721
A fellow scientist!

05:30.765 --> 05:32.375
What are the odds?

05:32.419 --> 05:33.985
What is it
that you do here?

05:34.029 --> 05:38.076
Uh, you have, uh,
stumbled on my work.

05:38.120 --> 05:42.603
I am, uh, I'm --
I'm creating a new world --

05:42.646 --> 05:44.082
a better one.

05:44.126 --> 05:47.259
My, uh,
my Utopia.

05:48.304 --> 05:51.263
But a utopia cannot be
a permanent place.

05:51.307 --> 05:54.136
It can exist
only as a hopeful state.

05:56.138 --> 05:59.359
You've read H.G. Wells.

06:00.403 --> 06:02.362
Oh, yes.

06:02.405 --> 06:04.929
No, he's --
he's one of my favorites.

06:06.453 --> 06:09.412
I-I read "A Modern Utopia"
when I was a kid.

06:09.456 --> 06:10.718
It inspired me.

06:10.761 --> 06:13.373
In fact,
I-I've been heavily influenced

06:13.416 --> 06:14.765
by the work of Wells.

06:14.809 --> 06:17.333
I-I consider him
something of a prophet

06:17.377 --> 06:19.770
because of his writing
of the future.

06:19.814 --> 06:23.383
Yes, he -- he certainly
was ahead of his time.

06:24.906 --> 06:27.952
Unshackle him.

06:27.996 --> 06:31.303
♪♪

06:35.743 --> 06:37.048
Go on, get up.

06:37.092 --> 06:38.398
I'm not your prisoner?

06:38.441 --> 06:40.182
No, no, of course not.

06:40.225 --> 06:42.402
It's been a long time
since I've had a conversation

06:42.445 --> 06:44.882
with a real intellect.

06:44.926 --> 06:48.451
Uh, come on,
I-I'll show you around.

06:55.371 --> 06:59.723
♪♪

07:03.771 --> 07:07.165
Welcome to
Project Utopia.

07:07.209 --> 07:11.256
♪♪

07:26.446 --> 07:30.450
♪♪

07:37.413 --> 07:38.588
Hello?

07:43.158 --> 07:47.118
♪♪

07:51.906 --> 07:52.950
♪♪

07:59.740 --> 08:00.958
♪♪

08:01.002 --> 08:04.484
Charming place,
don't you think?

08:04.527 --> 08:05.528
John?

08:05.572 --> 08:07.878
Brooke sent you here, too?

08:07.922 --> 08:09.532
Yes.

08:09.576 --> 08:13.318
I've already been attacked twice
by her deranged experiments.

08:13.362 --> 08:15.233
♪♪

08:16.757 --> 08:19.890
I don't think
these are Brooke's experiments.

08:19.934 --> 08:22.110
I think
they're her father's.

08:22.153 --> 08:24.112
So we went
backwards in time.

08:24.155 --> 08:25.896
Brooke is trying
to change the past.

08:25.940 --> 08:27.419
How?

08:27.463 --> 08:29.117
This is the book
that H.G. wrote, or will write.

08:29.160 --> 08:30.684
This is
"The Island of Dr. Moreau,"

08:30.727 --> 08:32.207
except
he changed the name.

08:32.250 --> 08:34.557
It's about a mad scientist
playing God,

08:34.601 --> 08:36.951
experimenting on animals
on an island.

08:36.994 --> 08:38.953
Oh, like father,
like daughter.

08:38.996 --> 08:42.086
She was using his journal
to do the same thing in 2017.

08:44.132 --> 08:46.569
I think
this is where you become

08:46.613 --> 08:48.832
the key ingredient
to Project Utopia.

08:48.876 --> 08:51.269
Over my dead body.

08:51.313 --> 08:52.749
That's the point.

08:52.793 --> 08:55.404
Not if
I find her father first

08:55.447 --> 08:57.798
and kill him
before he gets his way with me.

08:57.841 --> 08:59.626
Then the story's
over and done.

08:59.669 --> 09:01.584
No.
You can't alter the past.

09:01.628 --> 09:02.585
You can't change it.

09:02.629 --> 09:03.847
Watch me.

09:03.891 --> 09:05.283
Please,
we have to find H.G.

09:05.327 --> 09:07.155
The time machine --
it landed in the water,

09:07.198 --> 09:08.635
and it blew us apart
and we got separated.

09:08.678 --> 09:11.289
How do you know
he didn't drown?

09:11.333 --> 09:12.639
H.G. didn't drown.

09:12.682 --> 09:14.510
He's alive,
and we just have to find him.

09:14.554 --> 09:15.816
"We,"
as in you and me?

09:15.859 --> 09:16.991
Yes!

09:17.034 --> 09:18.558
For someone
who despises me,

09:18.601 --> 09:21.517
you're certainly quick
to turn to me for help.

09:21.561 --> 09:23.606
I don't need
your help.

09:23.650 --> 09:24.955
♪♪

09:28.393 --> 09:31.571
Look, I don't want to be
on this bloody island

09:31.614 --> 09:33.050
any longer
than you do,

09:33.094 --> 09:37.446
so let's find H.G.
and get the hell out of here.

09:40.667 --> 09:43.713
Here you go.

09:43.757 --> 09:45.106
Thank you.

09:47.717 --> 09:49.676
These people --
they all live here?

09:49.719 --> 09:52.853
Yeah, my staff
and volunteers.

09:52.896 --> 09:55.725
I've assembled the
best and the brightest
from my test trials.

09:55.769 --> 09:59.555
And we've created
a harmonious way of living.

09:59.599 --> 10:03.341
We all work together because
we all believe in the mission.

10:03.385 --> 10:04.691
Utopia?

10:04.734 --> 10:07.911
Yeah, Utopia.

10:09.478 --> 10:11.523
What type
of test trials, exactly?

10:11.567 --> 10:14.352
What do you know about the field
of genetic engineering?

10:14.396 --> 10:16.833
That it's man's latest attempt
to improve biological function.

10:16.877 --> 10:20.576
Yeah, and -- and what is
the logical, uh, conclusion

10:20.620 --> 10:22.360
of that work, hmm?

10:22.404 --> 10:26.234
Uh, to increase our strengths,
to decrease our weaknesses,

10:26.277 --> 10:30.934
to get rid of all
human suffering and discontent.

10:30.978 --> 10:33.371
Interfering with evolution?

10:33.415 --> 10:35.896
Darwin would be very interested
in your supposition.

10:35.939 --> 10:37.593
Wait, uh, it's more than
a supposition.

10:37.637 --> 10:40.770
No, we have seen
some incredible results.

10:40.814 --> 10:43.425
What exactly
have you accomplished?

10:43.468 --> 10:47.603
Uh, sorry to tease,
but, uh, the exact results

10:47.647 --> 10:49.213
are under lock and key

10:49.257 --> 10:51.085
unless you have some kind
of government clearance

10:51.128 --> 10:52.782
that I don't know about.

10:53.783 --> 10:56.612
You have
a great deal of security

10:56.656 --> 10:58.962
for such
a peaceful place.

10:59.006 --> 11:01.704
It's a
government-funded project,

11:01.748 --> 11:05.577
so they want me to, you know,
protect their investment.

11:05.621 --> 11:07.057
From what?

11:07.101 --> 11:09.973
Is there something dangerous
on this island?

11:10.017 --> 11:12.323
Yeah, there is.

11:12.367 --> 11:15.065
♪♪

11:15.109 --> 11:19.635
But you're safe here,
so why worry?

11:19.679 --> 11:22.246
Unless there's someone else
out there.

11:22.290 --> 11:24.335
I was stranded alone.
I can assure you --

11:24.379 --> 11:26.294
I can assure you...

11:26.337 --> 11:28.688
that I miss nothing.

11:28.731 --> 11:32.082
This compound is secure
because I am responsible

11:32.126 --> 11:35.129
for the safety of every
human being on this island.

11:35.172 --> 11:37.000
♪♪

11:38.001 --> 11:40.612
You need
to trust me, George.

11:40.656 --> 11:43.093
You need
to be a good guest.

11:43.137 --> 11:44.834
I'm a man
of curiosity, is all.

11:44.878 --> 11:46.357
My apologies
if you thought otherwise.

11:46.401 --> 11:48.751
Oh, Wellsley!

11:48.795 --> 11:53.321
This is my chief technician,
Robert Holland.

11:53.364 --> 11:54.975
Welcome.

11:55.018 --> 11:58.021
Uh, I'm sorry, sir.

11:58.065 --> 11:59.719
No luck
with the radar.

12:00.763 --> 12:02.852
We have
a radar system

12:02.896 --> 12:05.333
that tracks every living thing
on the island.

12:05.376 --> 12:07.117
It was damaged
a few days ago.

12:07.161 --> 12:08.945
Right, and no one
can repair it?

12:08.989 --> 12:10.294
I'm a little
out of my element.

12:10.338 --> 12:14.342
We -- We lost
our systems engineer.

12:14.385 --> 12:16.866
I actually have some experience
with electronics.

12:16.910 --> 12:18.520
Perhaps I could
have a look at it.

12:18.563 --> 12:20.043
It's...It's the least
I could do

12:20.087 --> 12:21.697
to pay you back
for your hospitality.

12:21.741 --> 12:23.699
♪♪

12:24.700 --> 12:26.833
Show Mr. Wellsley
what's wrong.

12:26.876 --> 12:30.750
It would be fantastic
if the radar could get fixed.

12:30.793 --> 12:32.229
Absolutely.

12:32.273 --> 12:33.665
This way.

12:35.058 --> 12:38.322
♪♪

12:42.065 --> 12:45.155
You sure letting him access
the radar is such a good idea?

12:45.199 --> 12:47.157
What have we got
to lose?
But what if
he decides --

12:47.201 --> 12:48.898
In two days,
the Department of Defense

12:48.942 --> 12:50.378
will be here --
in two days.

12:50.421 --> 12:52.336
The minute that they are,
I am screwed.

12:52.380 --> 12:54.077
The only way
that we can make sure

12:54.121 --> 12:55.687
that they don't find out
what I'm doing

12:55.731 --> 12:58.081
is to catch those animals
out there --

12:58.125 --> 13:00.692
catch them
and exterminate them.

13:00.736 --> 13:04.087
And I can't kill them
unless I can find them.

13:05.306 --> 13:07.743
♪♪

13:15.882 --> 13:18.536
Where's Robert?

13:18.580 --> 13:24.281
Uh...he's, um,
he's working on the radar.

13:25.761 --> 13:28.851
♪♪

13:29.896 --> 13:32.637
He might be there
a little while.

13:34.074 --> 13:35.640
Edward, please.

13:36.816 --> 13:39.775
We need to be...
more careful.

13:39.819 --> 13:41.429
I don't care.

13:41.472 --> 13:43.039
I didn't think
youcared.He's my husband.

13:43.083 --> 13:45.563
I'm not trying
to purposely hurt him.

13:45.607 --> 13:48.523
Then send him away to
take care of that kid you made.

13:48.566 --> 13:50.830
We won't have to
sneak around anymore.

13:51.874 --> 13:52.919
You need to focus.

13:52.962 --> 13:54.572
You're drinking
too much.

13:54.616 --> 13:55.835
Mm!

13:55.878 --> 13:56.879
It's one of
life's little joys.

13:56.923 --> 13:58.315
Come on, join me.
No.

13:58.359 --> 14:00.056
Did you speak
to the D.O.D.?

14:00.100 --> 14:02.667
Did you call
General Pratt?
I spoke
to his office.

14:02.711 --> 14:04.017
And did you tell them
not to come?

14:04.060 --> 14:05.757
I left word.Then they're still coming.

14:05.801 --> 14:07.759
They're gonna be here
in two days.

14:07.803 --> 14:08.891
♪♪

14:08.935 --> 14:10.197
You should be worried!

14:10.240 --> 14:11.589
What if they see
what you're doing?

14:11.633 --> 14:12.808
I'll handle it.

14:12.852 --> 14:15.028
How?
They could pull your funding.

14:15.071 --> 14:16.246
They could
shut us down.

14:16.290 --> 14:17.552
That's not
gonna happen!

14:17.595 --> 14:19.119
I'll do
what I always do,

14:19.162 --> 14:21.164
you know,
a little song and dance.

14:21.208 --> 14:23.210
Edward, please,
this is different.

14:23.253 --> 14:25.299
You have escaped patients
on this island.

14:25.342 --> 14:26.909
If they discover --

14:26.953 --> 14:28.389
Stop badgering me!

14:28.432 --> 14:29.912
I'll handle it.

14:29.956 --> 14:31.479
Let's not fight.

14:31.522 --> 14:35.135
♪♪

14:37.877 --> 14:39.443
We are...

14:39.487 --> 14:41.663
♪♪

14:41.706 --> 14:43.621
...on the cusp...

14:43.665 --> 14:46.494
of revolutionizing science.

14:53.936 --> 14:57.679
Oh,
you must be George.

14:57.722 --> 15:00.812
I'm Dr. Monroe's nurse,
Phyllis.

15:00.856 --> 15:02.118
My wife.

15:02.162 --> 15:05.165
Mrs. Holland,
you -- you live here too?

15:05.208 --> 15:09.734
Yes, we've been with the doctor
since he came to the island.

15:09.778 --> 15:10.953
George, drink?

15:10.997 --> 15:13.608
Oh, no, no, thank you.
Uh...

15:15.001 --> 15:16.306
Are these
your children?

15:16.350 --> 15:19.309
Yeah -- my son, Griffin,
my daughter, Brooke.

15:19.353 --> 15:21.833
You must
miss them very much.Yeah, sometimes.

15:21.877 --> 15:24.532
Actually, I have some hope,
uh...

15:24.575 --> 15:26.534
for Brooke.

15:26.577 --> 15:28.971
She has a-a quality
about her --

15:29.015 --> 15:30.842
reminds me of myself.

15:30.886 --> 15:33.367
Griffin, eh,
I don't know.

15:33.410 --> 15:36.457
There's not,
you know, so much there.

15:36.500 --> 15:39.547
And -- And do you
have children, too?

15:39.590 --> 15:41.505
A son, Chad.

15:41.549 --> 15:44.508
But a remote island
is no place for a small child.

15:44.552 --> 15:45.901
What's going on
with the radar?

15:46.902 --> 15:49.687
Uh, I'm afraid the problem
lies with the antenna,

15:49.731 --> 15:52.038
and I'd -- I'd like
to head there now if I could.

15:52.081 --> 15:53.430
That's impossible,
isn't it?

15:53.474 --> 15:56.694
It's too dangerous
at night.

15:56.738 --> 15:58.870
I don't understand.
Why is it so dangerous?

15:58.914 --> 16:01.699
There are, uh, experiments
out there that, uh --

16:01.743 --> 16:03.701
they wouldn't be very happy
to see you.

16:03.745 --> 16:05.225
I -- I don't understand.

16:05.268 --> 16:08.054
It's trial and error, my friend.

16:08.097 --> 16:10.534
And the errors
just, eh, wander off.

16:10.578 --> 16:14.016
What the doctor's saying is,
some of

16:14.060 --> 16:19.195
our volunteer test subjects are
living outside of the compound.

16:19.239 --> 16:20.544
Without treatment,

16:20.588 --> 16:22.590
they're beginning
to experience withdrawal.

16:22.633 --> 16:23.983
They're cuckoo,
and dangerous!

16:24.026 --> 16:25.245
Not all of them.

16:25.288 --> 16:26.550
Well, we tried
to find them all,

16:26.594 --> 16:29.379
but our radar
got sabotaged by Hudson.

16:29.423 --> 16:31.729
Hudson was our engineer.

16:31.773 --> 16:35.733
Hudson and the doctor
had a disagreement, and --

16:35.777 --> 16:38.214
He flew the coop!
He took off!

16:38.258 --> 16:39.911
He betrayed me!

16:39.955 --> 16:41.652
Edward.

16:42.697 --> 16:43.915
Fine.

16:43.959 --> 16:47.615
I'll have Montgomery
escort you

16:47.658 --> 16:50.400
to the radar tower
in the morning.

16:50.444 --> 16:52.011
The sooner
this thing gets fixed,

16:52.054 --> 16:54.230
the sooner I don't
have to think about it anymore.

17:08.288 --> 17:11.421
Push the embers towards
the center as I add the kindle.

17:12.901 --> 17:15.034
Careful --
not too much.

17:15.077 --> 17:17.471
We don't want
to draw attention to ourselves.

17:17.514 --> 17:20.430
It's not the first time
I've stared a fire, my dear.

17:20.474 --> 17:23.346
How do you think we heated
our houses in the 1800s?

17:26.697 --> 17:31.050
How does a girl like you
know how to build a fire?

17:31.093 --> 17:32.399
I grew up in Texas.

17:32.442 --> 17:34.966
My dad taught me how to shoot,
how to hunt,

17:35.010 --> 17:38.318
how to build a campfire.

17:38.361 --> 17:40.798
I probably spent more time
in the woods than you have.

17:40.842 --> 17:43.105
Yes, you probably have.

17:43.149 --> 17:45.977
Well, I find
an urban environment

17:46.021 --> 17:48.632
more suited
to my temperament.

17:48.676 --> 17:51.548
Ironic, since you're probably
just as savage

17:51.592 --> 17:53.072
as all the other monsters
on this island.

17:53.115 --> 17:55.378
Savage enough
to save your life.

17:57.511 --> 17:59.904
I'm the victim
in all of this.

17:59.948 --> 18:03.560
I'm the one who's been poked
and prodded against my will.

18:03.604 --> 18:06.911
You never did tell us what
Brooke did to you in her lab.

18:06.955 --> 18:09.697
I was unconscious
for most of it.

18:09.740 --> 18:12.656
She was very interested
in my DNA --

18:12.700 --> 18:15.094
my genetic makeup.

18:17.096 --> 18:20.142
We have to find H.G.

18:20.186 --> 18:22.405
Well, if we've not
come across him so far,

18:22.449 --> 18:24.015
I'm sure
he's either drowned

18:24.059 --> 18:27.193
or been killed
by one of those creatures.

18:27.236 --> 18:29.151
Are you trying
to cheer me up?

18:29.195 --> 18:31.936
I'm merely
considering the facts.

18:33.416 --> 18:35.679
I'm gonna get
some water.

18:54.263 --> 18:56.396
♪♪

18:57.962 --> 19:00.226
♪♪

19:00.269 --> 19:02.402
John?

19:09.713 --> 19:12.412
I don't see anything.

19:15.197 --> 19:17.243
There's something
out there.

19:20.202 --> 19:23.249
Here, take this.

19:24.946 --> 19:27.775
I've got my knife.

19:29.255 --> 19:34.869
♪♪

19:41.658 --> 19:42.920
Is there something

19:42.964 --> 19:44.879
you wish to say to me,
Mr. Montgomery?

19:44.922 --> 19:47.403
Shipwrecked
oceanographer, my ass.

19:47.447 --> 19:49.231
You're here
for a reason.I can assure you,

19:49.275 --> 19:51.059
coming to this place
was in no way my intention.

19:51.102 --> 19:53.627
I'll be more than happy
to leave.

19:55.150 --> 19:56.412
How doesone leave?

19:56.456 --> 19:58.501
Do you have boats
and a dock somewhere?

19:58.545 --> 20:00.590
Like I would tell you.

20:05.900 --> 20:07.510
♪♪

20:09.295 --> 20:12.167
♪♪

20:12.211 --> 20:13.516
George,
get to the radar tower.

20:13.560 --> 20:15.823
There's a guard there.
Go, we got this!

20:19.479 --> 20:23.526
♪♪

20:23.570 --> 20:25.311
Hey,
we were attacked!

20:25.354 --> 20:27.138
They need your help.
They're on the path.

20:30.403 --> 20:38.324
♪♪

20:51.119 --> 20:54.209
♪♪

20:55.428 --> 20:56.907
Who are you?

20:56.951 --> 20:59.040
I mean you no harm.

20:59.083 --> 21:01.042
You're not
from the compound.

21:02.130 --> 21:03.740
My name
is George Wellsley.

21:03.784 --> 21:06.047
Dr. Monroe sent me to fix
the radar tracking system.

21:06.090 --> 21:07.396
I can't
let you do that.

21:07.440 --> 21:09.224
I can assure,
I have no allegiance

21:09.268 --> 21:11.182
to either side
in your fight with Monroe.

21:11.226 --> 21:12.619
If you activate
the radar,

21:12.662 --> 21:15.186
it'll allow him
to find everyone who escaped.

21:15.230 --> 21:16.492
He'll kill us all.

21:16.536 --> 21:18.059
Why would he do that?

21:18.102 --> 21:19.539
He doesn't want the D.O.D.
to know

21:19.582 --> 21:20.888
what he's really
doing here.

21:20.931 --> 21:22.411
It's a research program.

21:22.455 --> 21:25.719
He's experimenting in ways
that aren't legal or moral.

21:25.762 --> 21:28.243
He is
making people crazy.

21:28.287 --> 21:30.027
Why should I believe you?

21:30.071 --> 21:31.942
My wife and I
worked for Monroe.

21:31.986 --> 21:34.249
Monroe has her.

21:34.293 --> 21:35.511
He spoke of you.

21:35.555 --> 21:37.034
You're Hudson,
his chief engineer.

21:37.078 --> 21:39.254
The D.O.D.
are arriving tomorrow.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.648
We just have to
make it through the night.

21:41.691 --> 21:43.258
So many people
need help.

21:43.302 --> 21:45.826
He will kill us
if he finds us.

21:45.869 --> 21:48.263
That includes
your friends --

21:48.307 --> 21:49.917
the girl
and the Englishman.

21:49.960 --> 21:51.788
You've seen her?
Where are they?

21:53.312 --> 21:55.139
Wellsley!Please, please, help us.

21:55.183 --> 21:58.404
♪♪

22:00.623 --> 22:03.060
Is it fixed?

22:03.104 --> 22:04.148
I can't repair it.

22:04.192 --> 22:05.541
Damn it.

22:05.585 --> 22:09.066
Okay,
we have to go -- now!

22:09.110 --> 22:10.894
♪♪

22:17.597 --> 22:19.729
It used to upset you
to come down here.

22:19.773 --> 22:22.297
Robert,
I'm trying to help them.

22:22.341 --> 22:24.081
You're helping Monroe
hurt them.

22:24.125 --> 22:25.779
He's crossed the line,
Phyllis.

22:25.822 --> 22:27.650
Just stop it,
Robert.

22:27.694 --> 22:30.349
He has become
completely unhinged.

22:30.392 --> 22:32.568
He's drinking
all the time.

22:32.612 --> 22:34.918
He's pushing the limits of what
he's doing with these people.

22:34.962 --> 22:36.224
They signed up for it.

22:36.267 --> 22:37.399
They knew
what they were getting into.

22:37.443 --> 22:38.400
No!

22:38.444 --> 22:39.793
They didn't.

22:39.836 --> 22:41.360
You used to believe
in what he was doing.

22:41.403 --> 22:42.752
No,
I believed in you.

22:44.319 --> 22:47.104
I believed the job would help us
provide for our family --

22:47.148 --> 22:48.454
for Chad.

22:49.455 --> 22:52.109
Well, I believe in the work
I'm doing here.

22:52.153 --> 22:54.590
I --
Dr. Monroe
is going to end

22:54.634 --> 22:56.418
disease and suffering
as we know it.

22:56.462 --> 22:58.115
This is bigger
than us.

22:58.159 --> 22:59.682
You got
to listen to me.

23:00.727 --> 23:02.685
We have to
get off this island.

23:02.729 --> 23:05.514
The D.O.D. is walking
in here tomorrow.

23:05.558 --> 23:07.777
They're gonna see
everything he's doing.

23:07.821 --> 23:09.692
And hopefully,
they'll see what a genius he is.

23:09.736 --> 23:12.652
Yeah, sure,
or a madman.

23:12.695 --> 23:15.437
Then maybe
you should leave.

23:15.481 --> 23:18.962
♪♪

23:19.006 --> 23:20.964
Are you
sleeping with him?

23:21.008 --> 23:25.142
♪♪

23:26.709 --> 23:29.625
What happened to us?

23:31.105 --> 23:34.238
We never
should've come here.

23:34.282 --> 23:37.241
What about our son?

23:37.285 --> 23:39.722
Do you even
think about him?

23:39.766 --> 23:44.074
The work we're doing here
is going to change the world.

23:44.118 --> 23:47.817
Everyone must
sacrifice something, Robert.

23:49.384 --> 23:54.650
♪♪

23:56.304 --> 23:59.655
How do we get inside?

24:01.048 --> 24:03.180
Come on, up we go.Oh, please.

24:03.224 --> 24:07.924
♪♪

24:17.064 --> 24:18.674
♪♪

24:20.720 --> 24:23.200
♪♪

24:23.244 --> 24:25.028
He's alive.

24:25.072 --> 24:26.682
Stay here.

24:29.555 --> 24:33.123
♪♪

24:39.260 --> 24:43.394
♪♪

24:45.614 --> 24:46.876
♪♪

24:46.920 --> 24:47.921
Hide.

24:47.964 --> 24:49.879
♪♪

24:49.923 --> 24:52.795
What are you doing
over there?

24:54.275 --> 24:55.450
Hello, there.

24:55.494 --> 24:57.104
Hold still.

24:57.147 --> 25:04.503
♪♪

25:15.339 --> 25:18.212
Mr. Wellsley.

25:18.255 --> 25:19.692
What's going on?

25:19.735 --> 25:22.216
I understand you haven't been
completely forthcoming

25:22.259 --> 25:23.696
about your situation.

25:23.739 --> 25:27.787
In what way?

25:29.658 --> 25:33.967
♪♪

25:35.490 --> 25:36.752
Who is this?

25:36.796 --> 25:38.580
Two Englishmen
wash up on my shore.

25:38.624 --> 25:40.277
Obviously,
there's some connection.

25:40.321 --> 25:42.584
I've never seen this man before
in my life.

25:42.628 --> 25:44.717
You're not
a very convincing liar,

25:44.760 --> 25:46.675
are you, Mr. Wellsley?
Mr. Montgomery...

25:48.634 --> 25:50.113
What do you plan on doing
with us?

25:50.157 --> 25:51.506
Oh, it's a surprise.

25:58.992 --> 26:02.778
♪♪

26:02.822 --> 26:05.172
Where's Jane?

26:05.215 --> 26:06.652
Hello to you, too, H.G.

26:06.695 --> 26:08.523
Please, John,
I know you were with her.

26:08.567 --> 26:09.611
Just tell me
where she is.

26:09.655 --> 26:11.004
I have no idea
where she is.

26:11.047 --> 26:12.701
We got separated
looking for you.

26:12.745 --> 26:15.138
♪♪

26:16.749 --> 26:20.709
♪♪

26:34.549 --> 26:41.121
♪♪

26:53.960 --> 26:57.964
♪♪

27:20.682 --> 27:22.423
David Anders, please.

27:22.466 --> 27:24.381
This is Robert Holland.

27:24.425 --> 27:27.558
No, it's imperative
I talk with him right away.

27:27.602 --> 27:29.778
Can you at least
get a message to him?

27:29.822 --> 27:31.475
Tell him...

27:31.519 --> 27:33.129
we're a go.

27:33.173 --> 27:35.871
As soon as I get off the island,
I will contact him.

27:35.915 --> 27:39.309
♪♪

27:44.184 --> 27:47.491
You deserve
a closer look at Project Utopia.

27:47.535 --> 27:50.799
This serum is a mixture
of -- of two key ingredients.

27:50.843 --> 27:54.498
Firstly -- and we have spared
absolutely, uh, no expense

27:54.542 --> 27:57.893
in assembling the finest
genetic material on Earth.

27:57.937 --> 28:00.069
The key
to unlocking its power

28:00.113 --> 28:02.332
is an enzyme
that I designed.

28:02.376 --> 28:05.596
It allows
the newly introduced DNA

28:05.640 --> 28:08.338
to move through the host's body
from cell to cell

28:08.382 --> 28:11.080
with greater speed
than anyone's ever seen.

28:11.124 --> 28:12.255
Dr. Monroe.

28:12.299 --> 28:14.518
Now, I have
a long way to go

28:14.562 --> 28:18.261
until the Utopia Project
fits its name.

28:19.480 --> 28:23.571
But I think it's best to be
up front about these things,

28:23.614 --> 28:26.617
especially, uh,
when there are guests.

28:28.184 --> 28:30.447
What do you want
from us?
What do I want
from you?

28:30.491 --> 28:31.753
I want you
to be honest.

28:31.797 --> 28:33.102
I want you to tell me
why you're here --

28:33.146 --> 28:34.669
what you want from me.

28:34.713 --> 28:37.628
♪♪

28:37.672 --> 28:39.761
H.G.,
for God's sake!

28:39.805 --> 28:42.111
Wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait!

28:42.155 --> 28:43.504
♪♪

28:43.547 --> 28:45.201
Spare his life,
and I will tell you

28:45.245 --> 28:46.768
how to fix
your radar tracking system.

28:46.812 --> 28:49.989
Someone unhooked the duplexer
from the antenna.

28:50.032 --> 28:53.993
You need it in order to both
receive and transmit data.

28:54.036 --> 28:56.952
I'll have it fixed
right away.

28:59.041 --> 29:02.871
Now, will you kindly put
the syringe away, doctor?

29:02.915 --> 29:04.960
No.

29:05.004 --> 29:07.354
I kindly
won't put the syringe away.

29:07.397 --> 29:09.965
This is gonna pinch.No, no, no, no, no.

29:10.009 --> 29:11.967
You bastard. You --

29:12.011 --> 29:13.534
Now, we just sit back
and watch the fun.

29:13.577 --> 29:15.492
What have you done
to him?

29:15.536 --> 29:17.016
♪♪

29:20.410 --> 29:24.327
♪♪

29:26.547 --> 29:30.551
♪♪

29:30.594 --> 29:32.161
Something's wrong.

29:32.205 --> 29:33.336
John?

29:33.380 --> 29:36.383
John,
are you all right?

29:36.426 --> 29:38.515
I've never
seen this before.

29:38.559 --> 29:42.824
The Utopia serum's
having absolutely no effect.

29:42.868 --> 29:45.348
And what
does that mean?

29:45.392 --> 29:47.786
What that means,
my dear boy,

29:47.829 --> 29:50.527
is you are something
very special.

29:50.571 --> 29:52.399
♪♪

29:58.753 --> 30:01.582
I need a chem panel
and those X-rays.

30:01.625 --> 30:04.324
We have so much to learn
from our friend here,

30:04.367 --> 30:05.804
and so little time.

30:05.847 --> 30:07.762
Leave me
the hell alone!Not a chance.

30:07.806 --> 30:09.285
Hold still --
ah, ah!

30:09.329 --> 30:10.939
Hold still.

30:10.983 --> 30:16.031
The enzyme had absolutely no
toxic effect on your brain,

30:16.075 --> 30:18.381
and if I can isolate
the immunity,

30:18.425 --> 30:21.515
you might be the key
to humanity's next step forward.

30:21.558 --> 30:23.604
You claim your mission
is Utopia,

30:23.647 --> 30:25.867
but all you're creating
is pain and suffering.

30:25.911 --> 30:27.390
Animals
are creatures of habit.

30:27.434 --> 30:29.044
Pain is just
a side effect to change,

30:29.088 --> 30:30.437
even on
the molecular level.

30:30.480 --> 30:31.742
The body's not designed
for this, doctor.

30:31.786 --> 30:33.222
There is a price to be paid

30:33.266 --> 30:35.050
for breaking
the laws of nature.

30:35.094 --> 30:36.878
Just look
at the violent psychosis

30:36.922 --> 30:38.314
you've created
in all your patients.

30:38.358 --> 30:40.403
Not with this one.

30:40.447 --> 30:43.406
Now, let's see
what happens

30:43.450 --> 30:47.019
if we combine his DNA
with the serum.

30:48.324 --> 30:49.891
You are
making a mistake.

30:49.935 --> 30:51.414
You don't know this man
as I do.

30:51.458 --> 30:52.894
He is
an unrepentant killer.

30:52.938 --> 30:55.157
You think I missed
his psychopathy, hmm?

30:55.201 --> 30:56.637
Did you wet the bed
as a child, hmm?

30:56.680 --> 30:57.812
I beg your pardon.

30:57.856 --> 30:58.857
I'll take that as a yes.

30:58.900 --> 31:00.075
Did you set
any fires?

31:00.119 --> 31:01.207
Did you torture
the family pet?

31:01.250 --> 31:02.773
Make your point.

31:02.817 --> 31:04.906
Mankind, uh, suffers
from a weakness of the mind.

31:04.950 --> 31:06.908
You're different.
Yours is strong.

31:06.952 --> 31:09.868
Now, he may have wasted
that gift on killing people.

31:09.911 --> 31:12.000
The rest of us
will do much better.

31:12.044 --> 31:14.568
Doctor, I too
know the thrill of discovery,

31:14.611 --> 31:16.744
and I understand
the hubris it can bring.

31:16.787 --> 31:19.834
But you cannot play God with a
mind as dark and twisted as his!

31:19.878 --> 31:24.273
Life is
survival of the fittest.

31:24.317 --> 31:25.622
♪♪

31:26.885 --> 31:30.236
My island
cannot escape the truth

31:30.279 --> 31:34.936
that all of us have
a little animal inside of us.

31:34.980 --> 31:36.459
What are you doing?

31:44.903 --> 31:46.121
What will happen
to him?

31:46.165 --> 31:47.601
If it works,

31:47.644 --> 31:50.386
he will reap the benefits
of Project Utopia --

31:50.430 --> 31:53.128
strength, reflexes,
cognition, perception.

31:53.172 --> 31:55.348
Trust me,
he'll want a lifetime supply.

31:55.391 --> 31:58.220
And if my blood
doesn't inoculate him?

31:58.264 --> 32:01.397
Then madness
will set in very quickly.

32:03.443 --> 32:06.707
♪♪

32:23.593 --> 32:26.205
Shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh, shh!

32:26.248 --> 32:29.512
You're here for the Brit
Monroe's keeping in his lab?

32:29.556 --> 32:30.513
Who are you?

32:30.557 --> 32:31.993
I'm not your enemy,

32:32.037 --> 32:34.561
but storming that lab
is suicide.

32:35.562 --> 32:37.042
Then what do I do?

32:37.085 --> 32:39.522
As soon as it's dark,
there will be a distraction.

32:39.566 --> 32:42.743
When Monroe's men respond,
that's when you go.

32:42.786 --> 32:44.614
What kind of distraction?

32:44.658 --> 32:46.312
You'll know.

32:49.097 --> 32:51.143
Wait for it.

32:53.754 --> 32:56.844
I need to show you something
on his X-ray.

32:56.887 --> 32:59.020
It could be nothing,
but...

32:59.064 --> 33:00.979
What the hell?

33:01.022 --> 33:04.895
It's a foreign object
buried in his shoulder.

33:04.939 --> 33:06.549
Where'd this man say
he was from again?

33:06.593 --> 33:07.986
He didn't.

33:08.029 --> 33:11.728
♪♪

33:11.772 --> 33:13.774
You're hiding something
from me.

33:13.817 --> 33:15.819
What are you
talking about?

33:15.863 --> 33:17.038
Aah!

33:17.082 --> 33:18.387
♪♪

33:18.431 --> 33:19.954
Aah!

33:19.998 --> 33:21.477
What is this?

33:21.521 --> 33:23.218
Whoever did this
picked a spot

33:23.262 --> 33:24.741
he may have never noticed
on himself.

33:24.785 --> 33:25.742
He may not know.

33:25.786 --> 33:27.657
Know what?

33:27.701 --> 33:29.094
Aah!

33:29.137 --> 33:31.748
All right.

33:31.792 --> 33:33.054
Easy.

33:34.490 --> 33:36.057
Easy.

33:36.101 --> 33:39.408
Aah! Aah!

33:39.452 --> 33:46.154
♪♪

33:50.985 --> 33:52.421
What is it?

33:52.465 --> 33:55.598
It's a microchip.

33:55.642 --> 33:58.862
♪♪

34:23.148 --> 34:25.106
Brooke.

34:25.150 --> 34:27.717
She must have
done this

34:27.761 --> 34:31.112
when I was captive
in her lab.

34:31.156 --> 34:34.289
♪♪

34:50.349 --> 34:53.874
She sent a message
to her father...

34:53.917 --> 34:55.832
to change the past.

34:55.876 --> 35:02.404
♪♪

35:05.712 --> 35:08.541
Tell Montgomery
to bring me Robert Holland!

35:08.584 --> 35:11.718
♪♪

35:13.720 --> 35:16.157
Edward,
what's going on?

35:18.203 --> 35:22.555
Your husband
is gonna betray us.

35:27.212 --> 35:28.691
Gentlemen,
sorry to keep you waiting.

35:28.735 --> 35:32.042
Now, what were we talking --
oh, I remember.

35:32.086 --> 35:34.697
You were just about to tell me
who you really are.

35:34.741 --> 35:36.699
♪♪

35:36.743 --> 35:39.093
All right,
let's start with you...

35:39.137 --> 35:41.269
Jack.

35:41.313 --> 35:46.144
Or -- Or do you, uh, prefer
Mr. Ripper or Dr. Ripper?

35:46.187 --> 35:47.275
Just John.

35:47.319 --> 35:48.711
Just John.

35:48.755 --> 35:50.887
Where's the fun in that --
just John?

35:50.931 --> 35:52.889
Why don't you take me
out of these restraints
and I'll show you.

35:52.933 --> 35:56.154
Enough!
Oh, and you!

35:57.764 --> 36:01.289
H.G. Wells --
you're on my island.

36:01.333 --> 36:02.682
What -- What an honor.

36:02.725 --> 36:04.684
The metaphilisophical irony
of this moment

36:04.727 --> 36:06.860
is blowing my mind.

36:06.903 --> 36:09.036
I mean, which came first --
the chicken or the egg?

36:09.079 --> 36:10.429
I mean,
I guess we'll never know.

36:10.472 --> 36:12.953
What was on that device
you pulled out of John?

36:12.996 --> 36:16.086
♪♪

36:16.130 --> 36:17.697
Y-You know what?

36:17.740 --> 36:19.264
Let's --
Let's play a game.

36:19.307 --> 36:20.395
What do you say?

36:20.439 --> 36:22.092
I-I'll take that
as a yes.

36:22.136 --> 36:23.224
True or false --

36:23.268 --> 36:24.660
you came here
from the future.

36:24.704 --> 36:26.009
♪♪

36:26.053 --> 36:28.011
From the year 2017.

36:28.055 --> 36:32.755
Um, uh, did I-I mention, uh,
the one who wins gets to live?

36:32.799 --> 36:35.105
True.

36:35.149 --> 36:36.498
Excellent!
We have a contestant.

36:36.542 --> 36:38.021
John, don't do this.

36:38.065 --> 36:39.936
He's lying to us.
He's gonna kill us regardless.

36:39.980 --> 36:41.895
Second question --

36:41.938 --> 36:44.463
you know my daughter,
Brooke?

36:44.506 --> 36:46.247
True.

36:49.294 --> 36:50.904
That's fantastic.

36:50.947 --> 36:54.124
All right,
final question --

36:54.168 --> 36:56.649
your time machine...

36:56.692 --> 36:58.781
is on my island?

36:58.825 --> 37:00.348
♪♪

37:00.392 --> 37:02.524
False.

37:02.568 --> 37:03.873
Ugh!

37:03.917 --> 37:04.787
Wrong! Wrong answer!

37:04.831 --> 37:06.354
No, no, it's true!

37:06.398 --> 37:07.964
We have no idea
where the time machine resides.

37:08.008 --> 37:09.749
No, no, no, no,
I'm sorry, game over.

37:09.792 --> 37:11.054
Rules are rules.
Guards!

37:11.098 --> 37:12.621
Guards!

37:12.665 --> 37:16.146
Take John
to the clinic.

37:16.190 --> 37:19.019
Tell them to prep him
for a blood draw.

37:19.062 --> 37:20.238
No.

37:20.281 --> 37:22.457
Tell 'em
I want all of it.

37:22.501 --> 37:25.155
Get your hands off me.

37:25.199 --> 37:26.809
Stop this madness.

37:26.853 --> 37:28.158
Please, please,
don't do this.

37:28.202 --> 37:30.509
Leave me
the hell alone!

37:30.552 --> 37:33.251
You want
to help your friend?

37:33.294 --> 37:35.905
Tell me where
that time machine is.

37:35.949 --> 37:37.820
I can't.
I don't know.

37:37.864 --> 37:41.259
Then I can't help you.

38:00.713 --> 38:03.411
♪♪

38:06.936 --> 38:10.418
♪♪

38:26.304 --> 38:30.133
♪♪

38:33.267 --> 38:35.269
Virginia?

38:43.408 --> 38:45.410
♪♪

38:47.673 --> 38:49.718
Ginny...

38:49.762 --> 38:51.285
we got to go.

38:51.329 --> 38:52.895
Come on.

38:52.939 --> 38:54.854
How many escaped?

38:54.897 --> 38:56.334
Eight.

38:56.377 --> 38:58.640
I need you to handle this
with extreme efficiency.

38:58.684 --> 39:00.120
You understand me?

39:00.163 --> 39:01.556
The D.O.D. will be here
tomorrow morning.

39:01.600 --> 39:02.992
They're gonna look
for any excuse they can find

39:03.036 --> 39:04.254
to shut us down.
Let's not give 'em one.

39:04.298 --> 39:06.082
Copy that.Did you find Robert?

39:06.126 --> 39:07.649
Not yet. My men are searching.
We'll find him!

39:09.521 --> 39:13.089
♪♪

39:20.880 --> 39:22.925
H.G.!

39:22.969 --> 39:25.101
Jane?
Oh, Jane.

39:25.145 --> 39:26.799
Aren't you a sight?

39:29.192 --> 39:31.369
What did they do
to you?

39:31.412 --> 39:34.284
Keys, keys --
the top left drawer.

39:35.808 --> 39:37.853
Got it.

39:43.381 --> 39:44.817
Hey!

39:44.860 --> 39:46.122
♪♪

39:48.516 --> 39:51.824
♪♪

39:53.652 --> 39:54.783
H.G.!

39:54.827 --> 39:57.046
Please stop,
that's enough!

39:57.090 --> 39:58.439
H.G...
Get back!

39:58.483 --> 40:00.789
♪♪

40:01.834 --> 40:03.836
H.G...

40:03.879 --> 40:05.533
No, no, no,
stay, stay.

40:05.577 --> 40:07.187
Don't come near me.

40:10.451 --> 40:13.411
♪♪

40:14.412 --> 40:16.979
Hey!
Stop right there!

40:17.023 --> 40:19.242
♪♪

40:20.461 --> 40:22.071
Robert!

40:22.115 --> 40:24.987
Are those
the Project Utopia files?

40:25.031 --> 40:26.119
Wait, Phyllis,
hear me out.

40:26.162 --> 40:28.556
Are you stealing
his research?

40:28.600 --> 40:31.472
This is our chance
to start over.

40:31.516 --> 40:32.821
Anders Enterprises --

40:32.865 --> 40:34.867
they'll pay us a fortune
for these documents.

40:34.910 --> 40:36.390
I can't believe
you're doing this.

40:36.434 --> 40:39.045
I'm doing this for us!
We need to leave this island.

40:39.088 --> 40:40.655
Get your hands
off me!

40:40.699 --> 40:44.093
♪♪

40:44.137 --> 40:46.661
I'm not
going anywhere.

40:46.705 --> 40:48.489
Please...

40:48.533 --> 40:50.752
come with me.

40:50.796 --> 40:52.319
Choose me.

40:52.362 --> 40:55.844
Choose our son
over him...

40:55.888 --> 40:58.020
over this chaos.

40:58.064 --> 41:01.459
♪♪

41:04.287 --> 41:06.681
The duplex is connected.
Give it a go.

41:09.162 --> 41:11.033
Ah, it's working.

41:11.077 --> 41:12.470
Okay, what are we
looking at?

41:12.513 --> 41:13.688
Uh, each of those blips
represents a person.

41:13.732 --> 41:16.299
I-I count...14.

41:16.343 --> 41:17.866
They're travelling
in small packs like animals.

41:17.910 --> 41:20.695
I need to take care of this
before the D.O.D. shows up.

41:20.739 --> 41:23.219
We don't have
much time.

41:23.263 --> 41:28.311
♪♪

41:31.445 --> 41:33.926
John!
Jane,
thank God.

41:33.969 --> 41:35.231
Are you okay?

41:35.275 --> 41:36.581
I'm fine.

41:36.624 --> 41:38.278
H.G. needs our help.

41:38.321 --> 41:40.236
Yes, I'm aware.

41:40.280 --> 41:41.411
What did
they do to him?

41:41.455 --> 41:43.544
Come on,
let's move.

41:43.588 --> 41:45.067
Tell me --
what did they do to him?

41:45.111 --> 41:46.416
We have to go, Jane.

41:46.460 --> 41:48.549
Hello, young lady.

41:48.593 --> 41:50.420
What's your name?

41:51.596 --> 41:53.075
What is your name?

41:53.119 --> 41:56.818
♪♪
